nd, the system has beendesigned to be as idiotproof as possible and is menu-driven, has few optionson the screen at any one time and doesn't trust physicians with a &quot;help&quot;facility.andP;  All operations are single key.andP;  The launch of the system istimely.andP;  The White Paper making resources management in hospitals mandatoryis due to come into effect in a year's time and a report published lastJanuary by the Royal College of Physicians states that all junior doctorsmust now receive some training in medical auditing.andP;  The system can be usedon any IBM compatible personal computer and can handle up to 2,000m patients'records.andP;  For four users the total package is #40,000, the software alonecosts #14,000.andP;  MicroM d Medical will beandM;available for installation from June.andO;</TEXT></DOC>